This 20 min prawn power bowl is so delish and perfect for a quick dinner if you’re short on time. Full recipe below!

*I forgot to film the rice, but use rice or any other base you would like (cauliflower rice, greens, ect.) 

In a bowl, add and mix:
8oz shrimp
1/2 tbsp avo oil
pinch of salt
1 tsp cayenne pepper
1/2 tbsp smoked paprika 
1/2 tbsp garlic powder 
Set aside. 

Sauce
In a small bowl add and mix:
1 minced garlic clove
1 tsp wasabi 
2 tbsp mayo
1 tbsp rice vinegar (I used apple cider vinegar)
Juice from half a lime
Pinch of salt

Prep your veggies:
Cucumber
Green onions
Avocado
Edamame beans (I used frozen ones from Whole Foods and cooked them in boiling water for 3 mins)

Heat avo oil over medium high heat and add prawns for approx. 60 seconds per side. 

Plate everything and drizzle sauce over top - enjoy !

Recipe by @shredhappens

Healthy Beef Stirfry | LOVE this one. It’s super easy to make - perfect for meal prep or a quick week night dinner. Recipe below 🫶🏼

Yields about 4 servings
Ingredients:
600g beef
1/2 onion
3 Bell Peppers
4 garlic cloves minced
3 green onions diced 
1 1/2 tbsp sesame oil
2 tbsp tomato sauce (low sodium)
2 tbsp BBQ Sauce
1 tbsp Rice Wine Vinegar 
1 tbsp Light Soy Sauce
Sesame seeds
Seaweed

Heat sesame oil over medium high heat and cook beef. Season with salt and pepper. 

Meanwhile cook rice. 

Once cooked, remove beef from pan and cook veggies until soft. 

In a small bowl mix garlic, tomato sauce, BBQ sauce, rice wine vinegar, and soy sauce. 

Drizzle sauce on top of veggies in pan and add beef. Simmer for 5-7 mins. 

Serve on top of rice and garnish with sesame seeds and green onion. 
Option to eat with seaweed. 
Enjoy :)

Recipe inspired by: @_aussiefitness

This is the Lemon Chicken of your dreams and it’s gluten free, dairy free and paleo. Full recipe below 🤤

Ingredients:
Avocado oil
1 lb chicken
1/2 yellow onion diced
4 garlic cloves minced
Zest from half a lemon
Juice from whole lemon 
1 cup vegetable broth (or other broth of choice)
1 cup canned coconut milk
1 tbsp arrowroot starch
Red pepper flakes

Season chicken with salt n pepper and heat large pan on med high heat. Once hot, add oil and chicken. Once chicken is cooked, remove from pan and set aside. 

In the same pan, turn heat down to medium, add oil and sauté the onions. After a few mins, add garlic and lemon zest, stir and cook for another minute. Turn heat to low, add broth and let simmer for a couple minutes before stirring in the coconut milk and arrowroot starch. Season with salt n pepper and optional red pepper flakes. 

Continue to let simmer until the sauce thickens and in the last few mins add the chicken back in. 

Serve over cauliflower rice with parsley mixed in - enjoy :)

Recipe inspired by: @munchinwithmaddie

I love Teambuildr especially when I’m travelling because it allows me to connect with a trainer who then creates personalized workouts/programming for me. I didn’t have access to a gym this day so I asked my trainer for an at home booty burner and he delivered! This is a great workout if you’re short on time/equipment but still want a good burn. If you live in Vancouver, check out @yardathletics_ and meet the amazing trainers behind Teambuildr 💪🏼
